  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hospital readmission rate following percutaneous coronary interventions (PCI) or coronary
      angiographies (CAG) is a main indicator of quality of care and addresses economic issues. The
      aim of this study is to quantify the frequency and analyse the types of rehospitalizations
      and repeat revascularizations during one year after a PCI or a CAG. This information is
      needed to organize the health care pathway and to identify preventable rehospitalizations.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
